# Pi-GATO Build Guide

## Clean Install + Full Working System Setup

Platform:

* Raspberry Pi 5
* Raspberry Pi OS Lite (64-bit)
* USB Numpad
* MPV
* Python EVDEV IPC Playback Engine

This guide installs a fully working Pi-GATO system from scratch.

---

# 1. FLASH THE OS

Use Raspberry Pi Imager.

Install:

```text id="p1xk4u"
Raspberry Pi OS Lite (64-bit)
```

DO NOT install desktop OS.

Pi-GATO is designed for:

* low overhead
* direct GPU rendering
* terminal operation

---

# 2. FIRST BOOT

Login to Raspberry Pi.

Update system:

```bash id="m8xq1z"
sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade -y
```

---

# 3. INSTALL REQUIRED PACKAGES

Install MPV + Python tools:

```bash id="s2z0ov"
sudo apt install -y \
mpv \
python3 \
python3-pip \
python3-venv \
ffmpeg
```

Purpose:

* mpv = video engine
* python3 = scripting
* pip = Python package manager
* venv = isolated Python environment
* ffmpeg = video utilities

